Transport Information: Brasilia
Brasilia will provide ticket holders free access on some special routes which run to the stadium. 
The lines providing free transport are:

•	108.6  – Plano Piloto bus station/Shopping Popular mall (every 15 mins)

•	109.7  – Plano Piloto bus station/Funarte (every 5 mins)

•	109.2 – Circular Parque da Cidade (every 5 mins) 

Fans arriving at Brasilia International Airport can use executive buses 0.113 or 113.1 which run between Aeroporto (Airport) and the Hotel Sectors (Setores Hoteleiros). Fans should alight at either the North or South Hotel Sector and proceed to the stadium on foot. Another route available is regular bus service 0.102 or 102.1 (Aeroporto/Rodoviaria) between the airport and the bus station. Alight at the bus station (Rodoviaria) and proceed to the stadium on foot. 
Bus service 109.7 is yet another option. Alight at FUNARTE and walk to the stadium. 
 
As the bus station is located near the stadium, it is possible to walk. The distance is around 1.8km. For those wanting to take a bus, service 109.7 follows the same route. Alight at FUNARTE and proceed to the stadium on foot. 
 
Take bus service 108.8 (Rodoviaria Interestadual/Rodoviaria de Brasilia) which runs from the interstate bus station to the main city bus station. Board at the stop next to the entrance to Estacao Shopping metro station. It leaves every 30 minutes. 
 
Use bus service 108.6 and alight at FUNARTE. From there, proceed to the stadium on foot. 
